# Services

Internal address = Docker network hostname (service-to-service calls).
External address = host browser access (HTTPS via Traefik + mkcert).

| Service | Internal address | External address | Notes |
|---------|------------------|------------------|-------|
| app     | `app:8000`       | `https://{{ project_slug }}.localhost` | FastAPI app; `/heartbeat`, `/health`, `/metrics` |
| traefik | `traefik:80/443` | `https://{{ project_slug }}.localhost` | Reverse proxy, TLS termination (dev profile) |
| prometheus | `prometheus:9090` | `http://localhost:9090` | Scrapes `app:8000/metrics`; loads SLO alert rules (dev profile) |
| grafana | `grafana:3000` | `http://localhost:3000` | SLO dashboard (auto-provisioned); anonymous admin in dev (dev profile) |
| alertmanager | `alertmanager:9093` | `http://localhost:9093` | Fires on SLO-breach alert rules; local null receiver (dev profile) |
| loki | `loki:3100` | `http://localhost:3100` | Log store; queried in Grafana (dev profile) |
| promtail | `promtail:9080` | (no host port) | Ships container logs to Loki via the Docker socket (dev profile) |

Run `task certs` once to generate the local mkcert certificate, then `task dev`.
